      <acqinfo id="aspace_7fbfe745f5cce3fa19abe5098debdc04">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of George W. Pierson, 1962. The papers were originally part of the Miscellaneous Manuscripts Collection, MS 352.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7c009d57b279f61110bf982e236eecf3">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Eliza D. Pierson Papers consist of correspondence, notes, and research material used by Eliza Pierson in compiling a history of the S. S. Seward Institute in Florida, New York for presentation to the local chapter of the Daughters of the American Revolution, ca. 1914. The manuscript and printed copy of the paper are in folder 1. The papers include printed catalogs of the school and program for public exercises of the Young Ladies Department dating from 1853 to 1928. A few other items relate to the Warwick (N.Y.) Historical Society.</p>
         <p>George W. Pierson donated his aunt's papers to the Yale Library in 1962. They were transferred from the Miscellaneous Manuscripts Collection in 1985.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <prefercite id="aspace_9863cc5d752e44df7a98d43c2ecc90f5">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Eliza D. Pierson Papers (MS 1428).  Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
